<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Arrhenatherum</i> <i>elatius</i>, <i>Cynosurus</i> <i>echinatus</i>, <i>Danthonia</i> <i>pilosa</i> and/or <i>Nassella</i> <i>manicata</i> is dominant or co-dominant with other non-natives in the herbaceous layer. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 50cm; cover is intermittent to continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Cynosurus echinatus</i> or <i>Arrhenatherum elatius</i> > 50% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Jimerson et al. 2000).</li>
		
		<li><i>Cynosurus echinatus, </i> and/or <i>Nassella manicata</i> >60% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Klein et al. 2015).</li>
		
		<li>With non-native plants > 90% relative cover overall, <i>Cynosurus echinatus, Danthonia pilosa (Rytidosperma penicillatum), </i>and/or <i>Nassella manicata</i> > 50% relative cover in the herbaceous layer, or two of these species > 60% relative cover combined (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> All slopes and aspects.  </div>
</div>

        
