<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Fluctuation in dominance by woody species and grasses in the northern Coast Ranges relates historically to fire intervals. However, intervals between fires before pre-European contact are very difficult to calculate. Because non-native grasses such as <i>Arrhenatherum elatius </i>and <i>Cynosurus echinatus </i>are now abundant, many of these calculations are unobtainable according to many experts (Young et al. 2007).</div>
